    "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>4-2-015</b>\n</p><p>Radio beacon schedule Sequence number\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\">A</span> term used in parts of the world where radio beacons are operated in groups. It indicates the position (or positions) in the group occupied by the transmissions of the radio beacon and is designated by the numbers) of the minute(<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"03c7c0ace395d80182db07ae2c30f034\">s</span>) in which transmission occurs.\n</p><p>Reference: <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\">A</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"d20caec3b48a1eef164cb4ca81ba2587\">L</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"e1e1d3d40573127e9ee0480caf1283d6\">R</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"5dbc98dcc983a70728bd082d1a47546e\">S</span>.\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>ampere\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"03c7c0ace395d80182db07ae2c30f034\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>second\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"d20caec3b48a1eef164cb4ca81ba2587\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Luminance\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Level (technician training - WWA)\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Latitude (in degrees)\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"e1e1d3d40573127e9ee0480caf1283d6\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Reserve buoyancy\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Reflected amplitude\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Range (also ρ)\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"5dbc98dcc983a70728bd082d1a47546e\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>South\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260616023110\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.039 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.057 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 60/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 806/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 281/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   13.975      1 -total\n 74.70%   10.440      1 Template:Languages\n 52.60%    7.350      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n 24.05%    3.361      1 Template:IALAFooter\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:1120-0!canonical and timestamp 20260616023110 and revision id 3175. Rendering was triggered because: api-parse\n -->\n</div>",
